    "description": "<span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><picture><source srcset=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1798690/extras/4ede79d8e9a8f609ac5d5f036e69fb27.apng?t=1753666667\"><img src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1798690/extras/4ede79d8e9a8f609ac5d5f036e69fb27.poster.avif?t=1753666667\" class=\"bb_img\" width=576 height=64 /></picture></span><br>Blackjack Avenue is a casual Casino Blackjack Simulation. <br><br>Enjoy the experience of being in a casino without the risk of spending real money.<br><br>Play Blackjack, also known as &quot;21&quot; by getting cards from the dealer.<br><br>The goal is to get a higher hand than the dealer. <br><br>But don't get more than 21, or else you will bust and the dealer wins!<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><picture><source srcset=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1798690/extras/9222db1069b911f9215a46a797dbaaf8.apng?t=1753666667\"><img src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1798690/extras/9222db1069b911f9215a46a797dbaaf8.poster.avif?t=1753666667\" class=\"bb_img\" width=576 height=64 /></picture></span><br><br>Use classic techniques such as Splitting Pairs, Double Down and Insurance.<br><br>Experiment with different betting / split strategies and see what works best for you. <br><br>The table has a 2K bet maximum.<br><br>There are no micro-transactions, or real money and you can play offline.<br><br>Use the Color buttons to split chips into smaller denominations if necessary.<br><br>Track your progress with the Stats page and improve your Blackjack skills!<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><picture><source srcset=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1798690/extras/4906287b9bc6b8ef40d888e10d695fed.apng?t=1753666667\"><img src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1798690/extras/4906287b9bc6b8ef40d888e10d695fed.poster.avif?t=1753666667\" class=\"bb_img\" width=576 height=64 /></picture></span><br><br>You can choose the amount of decks used.<br><br>Options for the amont of decks include 1, 2, 4, or 6 decks. <br><br>Use the pixel-art ATM for more chips which draw against your profile's digital balance.<br><br>It's ok to have a negative balance. <br><br>If you feel your balance went too negative, simply reset via profile options and try again.<br><br>You're invited to Blackjack Avenue! Where your next BIG WIN is just a click away!",
